'''Cam Clarke''' (born [[November 6]], [[1950s|1957]]) is an American voice actor and singer. He has provided voices for various ''Star Wars'' video games, as well as the fan project ''TROOPS''.

In addition to his ''Star Wars'' roles, he is well known for his long list of video game and animation roles, playing the characters [[Wowwiki:Medivh|Medivh]] and [[Wowwiki:Malygos|Malygos]] in [[Wowwiki:World of Warcraft|''World of Warcraft'']], Liquid Snake in [[Wikipedia:Metal Gear Solid|''Metal Gear Solid'']], [http://aselia.wikia.com/wiki/Kratos_Aurion Kratos Aurion] in the English dub of ''[http://aselia.wikia.com/wiki/Tales_of_Symphonia Tales of Symphonia]'', Kaneda in US dub of ''[[Wikipedia:Akira (film)|Akira]]'', Simba's singing voice in [[Wikipedia:The Lion King II: Simba's Pride|''The Lion King II: Simba's Pride'']], Leonardo in the [[Wikipedia:Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 TV series)|''Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles'']], and Krelian in ''Xenogears''. Cam also was the voice of Herren in EA's ''Dragon Age: Origins'' and ''Dragon Age: Origins-Awakening'' and related DLC.

==Biography==
Cam Clarke was born in 1957 in the city of Los Angeles, California to actor [[Wikipedia:Robert Clarke|Robert Clarke]] and singer [[Wikipedia:The King Sisters|Alyce King]]. Cam's first entry into show business was his appearances on his family's ABC variety show ''The King Family'' at the age of six. He continued to perform with his family on various TV specials until the 1980s when he got his first voice acting roles in the animated shows ''[[Wikipedia:Snorks|Snorks]]'' and ''[[Wikipedia:Robotech (TV series)|Robotech]]''.

